        Larry Joe Hunter 05/21/2001 03:28 PM       To: Mark Taylor/HOU/ECT@ECT, Sara Shackleton/HOU/ECT@ECT  cc:   Subject: AEP Master Amendments


Mark/Sara,


We are attempting to get two amendments to the ISDA with AEP right now.  Mark, you are working on the Amendment allowing for EOL Transactions to not need written Confirmations and Sara is working on an amendment that will change the Confirming Party to ENA (for some reason, AEP was allowed to be the Confirming Party when the Master was drafted.)   At any rate, is it possible that we send both of these amendments to AEP at the same time?  We want to make sure that AEP views these amendments together and sign off on both.  We think they'll be more comfortable signing them both at once rather than a couple of weeks apart.


Let me know.


Thanks,

Joe Hunter
